---
presentation: poster
layout: letter-flyer
title: Greater Houston Stamp Show
subtitle: September 18–20, 2026
author: Houston Philatelic Society
themes: [light]
evaluation: dynamic
event:
  name: Greater Houston Stamp Show
  dates: September 18–20, 2026
  url: https://houstonstampclub.org/greater-houston-stamp-show-2026/
  venue: Humble Civic Center
  address_line1: 8233 Will Clayton Pkwy
  address_line2: Humble, TX 77338
  hours:
    - day: Friday 18th
      time: 10–6
    - day: Saturday 19th
      time: 10–5
    - day: Sunday 20th
      time: 10–4
  stamp_release:
    name: Winter Wreath
    kind: Global Forever stamp
    photographer: Natalia Kostikova
    designer: Greg Breeding
    release: Friday 18th at 11:00 AM
    stamp_image: winter-wreath-2026.png
    lead: A snowy holiday wreath for the season’s Global Forever issue.
    summary: >-
      Photographer Natalia Kostikova built the wreath from artificial branches
      and craft-store materials, painting each ornament and dusting the greenery
      with baking soda for frost. Designed by Greg Breeding for the United
      States Postal Service.
  auction:
    kind: Donation silent auction
    highlight: "US Scott #91, 15¢ Lincoln with E-Grill"
    stamp_image: ../samples/SC91.jpg
    bidding_starts: Saturday 19th 10:00 AM
    closes: "Sunday 20th, 3:00 PM"
    terms: Whole-dollar cash bids only
    lead: A curated premium selection of donated lots to support the show.
    summary: >-
      Highlight lot US Scott #91, the 15¢ Lincoln with E-Grill — a classic-era
      issue that anchors this year’s GHSS donation auction.
---
